        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<p class="sqsrte-large">SEO may be the most important technique for a business in reaching new customers. With user-experience being such a significant customer retention factor, improving your SEO may be a great way to give your small business a competitive advantage over your competitors.&nbsp;</p><p class="sqsrte-large">Here are a few SEO strategies that can ensure your small business will prosper this coming year!&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>1. Increase the speed of your website&nbsp;</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">In July 2018, Google released a statement that <strong>mobile page speed is the number one factor used to determine web page rankings</strong>. With the increasing use of technology, page speed is more important than ever. Google’s <a href="https://developers.google.com/speed/pagespeed/insights/"><em>PageSpeed Insights</em></a> tool is a simple way to test out the current speed of your webpages.&nbsp;</p><p class="sqsrte-large">One simple way you can improve your website speed is by decreasing the size of the images on your website:&nbsp;</p><p class="sqsrte-large">• By compressing the size of images, the browser will take less time to appear without compromising the quality of the image.&nbsp;</p>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1615827707352-NPCNK2OXVRCLZJ963Z86/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kNZrSGJ2aM5uGcJPqRn_vAtZw-zPPgdn4jUwVcJE1ZvWQUxwkmyExglNqGp0IvTJZUJFbgE-7XRK3dMEBRBhUpy6peidHYs5a4dPF9R4rhlQeusnJUfSvwpDSPLhqLqSpoMRwOb2-iO9LclRuyjzZ7c/adlibweb.jpg" data-image-dimensions="626x417" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="adlibweb.jpg" data-load="false" data-image-id="604f92fb132d35773fc528e5" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1615827707352-NPCNK2OXVRCLZJ963Z86/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kNZrSGJ2aM5uGcJPqRn_vAtZw-zPPgdn4jUwVcJE1ZvWQUxwkmyExglNqGp0IvTJZUJFbgE-7XRK3dMEBRBhUpy6peidHYs5a4dPF9R4rhlQeusnJUfSvwpDSPLhqLqSpoMRwOb2-iO9LclRuyjzZ7c/adlibweb.jpg?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<h3><strong>2. Create a “Google+ Local” &amp; “Google Places” Page</strong>&nbsp;</h3><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>The strongest way for any business to grow is through the support of its community</strong>. According to Zero Zen Data, 70% of customers trust reviews from unknown users on platforms such as Google Places, Local, Yahoo, and Yelp. The impact that external reviews have upon a business’s ability to grow is immense and one positive review could bring an influx of loyal customers to your brand. Creating a Google+ Local or Places page is particularly beneficial for improving SEO, because it will also help you to make sure the correct business information is being shared with the web/your community.&nbsp;Learn more about Google+ Local and Google Places, <a href="https://www.searchenginewatch.com/2013/09/06/google-places-for-business-vs-google-local/">here</a>. </p>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
