            <p class=""><em>Example of a Google Places page for a business: includes business information + reviews section</em></p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<h3><strong>3. Drive new clients through Long-tail search</strong>&nbsp;</h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Identifying search keywords is a popular technique businesses use to increase SEO, but there is a more effective strategy that is lesser known and more strategic: Long-tail search. <strong>Long-tail search queries have been stated to be twice as effective at attracting customers when compared to keywords</strong>. The difference between search queries and keywords may be confusing at first, but can be easily understood through the definitions below:&nbsp;</p><p class="sqsrte-large"><span>Query:</span> A statement searched up by a user, that derives a relevant and helpful result. The query loses relevance as an applicable search appears.&nbsp;</p><p class="sqsrte-large"><em>Example: (A user searches) Best Socks under $25&nbsp;</em></p><p class="sqsrte-large"><span>Keyword:</span> A phrase that a user types that businesses try to rank high for, in order to appear in the top ten displayed results.&nbsp;</p><p class="sqsrte-large"><em>Example: (A user searches) Best socks&nbsp;</em></p>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          <a class="
                sqs-block-image-link
                
          
        
              " href="https://neilpatel.com/blog/long-tail-keywords-seo/"
              
          >
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1615827969091-6U74I21GMCN4PULB7QGW/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kHLPrZX37jrO9I4_j9iGoYgUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcyG5gR7L7ZvhYL9x7-M0mikDnrZforqZ_5iEopMruFA7l_AYb9Fp9fGMguHr0vQK7/Screen+Shot+2021-03-15+at+1.05.30+PM.png" data-image-dimensions="1222x840" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="Neil Patel: 11 Reasons to Focus on Long-Tail Keywords for SEO    (Neil Patel is a NYT best-selling author + top web influencer)" data-load="false" data-image-id="604f9400b7dd892ae1213b93" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1615827969091-6U74I21GMCN4PULB7QGW/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kHLPrZX37jrO9I4_j9iGoYgUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcyG5gR7L7ZvhYL9x7-M0mikDnrZforqZ_5iEopMruFA7l_AYb9Fp9fGMguHr0vQK7/Screen+Shot+2021-03-15+at+1.05.30+PM.png?format=1000w" />
          
        
