          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<p class="sqsrte-large">The <em>specificity </em>of long-term search queries is what Google’s SEO analytics determine as a <em>ranking factor</em>.&nbsp;</p><p class="sqsrte-large">Still not convinced?&nbsp;</p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Long-tail queries are stated to send 70% more traffic to websites and blogs</strong>.&nbsp;</p><p class="sqsrte-large">If you are a small business owner without a big budget, this serves as a great opportunity!&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>4. Increase the use of internal links</strong>&nbsp;</h3><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Increasing the number of internal links on your site can have a direct effect on Google's ranking</strong>. Internal links are defined as links that connect one page on a domain to another page on the same domain — in other words, including links on your site pages that link to other pages on your site.</p><p class="sqsrte-large">So, what pages should have more internal links?&nbsp;</p><p class="sqsrte-large">Using google analytics, find the pages on your site that are in the 2nd-4th ranking. These pages are powerful because they already drive a significant amount of traffic. Therefore, including more internal links on these pages may increase your chances of improving your site’s PageRank (Google’s way of measuring the importance of website pages).&nbsp;</p>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1615828232457-FRBAUHGH917BKSU716UR/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kHInGRCZ0vVblPmDbfwOtZ1Zw-zPPgdn4jUwVcJE1ZvWQUxwkmyExglNqGp0IvTJZUJFbgE-7XRK3dMEBRBhUpzv-pgQXlGP9Nbo9Gtw5Kqjo6yt8cf4uADH7r8QW1PIQM70s7DeOCksQevcYE_Far0/image02-2.jpg" data-image-dimensions="728x298" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="image02-2.jpg" data-load="false" data-image-id="604f95087cbde54418bc631e" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1615828232457-FRBAUHGH917BKSU716UR/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kHInGRCZ0vVblPmDbfwOtZ1Zw-zPPgdn4jUwVcJE1ZvWQUxwkmyExglNqGp0IvTJZUJFbgE-7XRK3dMEBRBhUpzv-pgQXlGP9Nbo9Gtw5Kqjo6yt8cf4uADH7r8QW1PIQM70s7DeOCksQevcYE_Far0/image02-2.jpg?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<h3><strong>5. Fix broken links and pages that are not working</strong>&nbsp;</h3><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Broken links can be one reason why website traffic tapers off</strong>. Broken backlinks can occur when a linking site has bugs, or when a page that has backlinks is deleted or moved.&nbsp;</p>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1615828364296-TX8U30VUOEFT0TLWK977/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kEhRb-mGDiEi0xC18_AR20gUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcsUFtfQr2yxuOzlidL-fYvTwqjsYaERXA-DujV44Tnn4ay3UZP6GxYjP38VLon1Vj/404-not-found-error-scanner-1.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1200x630" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="An example of what a page might look like to a viewer on the internet if you have a broken link on your site." data-load="false" data-image-id="604f958c6f8f551ed049625e" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1615828364296-TX8U30VUOEFT0TLWK977/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kEhRb-mGDiEi0xC18_AR20gUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcsUFtfQr2yxuOzlidL-fYvTwqjsYaERXA-DujV44Tnn4ay3UZP6GxYjP38VLon1Vj/404-not-found-error-scanner-1.jpg?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
          
          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p class=""><em>An example of what a page might look like to a viewer on the internet if you have a broken link on your site.</em></p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<p class="sqsrte-large">Here are a few techniques to fix a broken link:&nbsp;</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Redirect the broken link to a new location:</strong> If a new URL is forgotten to be redirected, implement a <a href="https://developers.google.com/search/docs/advanced/crawling/301-redirects"><span>301 direct</span></a> (code used to show that a page within your website has been permanently moved to a new location) after finding a new page location.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Redirect the broken link to a pre-existing, relevant page:</strong> Redirect the 404 page (code for stating that the server could not find the requested page) to a similar, pre-existing webpage within your domain (on your site).&nbsp;</p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Restore the page:</strong> If the page is killed, this will be the fastest way to fix a broken link. Only restore the page if the content is considered relevant.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Recreate the broken page:</strong> Create a new page and direct the broken link to it.&nbsp;</p><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class=""></p></li></ul>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1615828447518-VSA0X5MY9081H8UWO5RA/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kPj2DCVms7d7tLeg9lnusy0UqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcllyDBk-Rde3pMfu1yxf_Wc5HRPacxUYz359yYmtIc1fpVHwiJ4D2r7J_oJbKCrQl/broken-links-building-2.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1000x500" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="broken-links-building-2.jpg" data-load="false" data-image-id="604f95dfc31f06552b0a9607" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1615828447518-VSA0X5MY9081H8UWO5RA/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kPj2DCVms7d7tLeg9lnusy0UqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcllyDBk-Rde3pMfu1yxf_Wc5HRPacxUYz359yYmtIc1fpVHwiJ4D2r7J_oJbKCrQl/broken-links-building-2.jpg?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


