<p class="sqsrte-large">Online reviews are often the go-to for potential customers looking to get a first impression of your business and they are a huge part of a business’s reputation. If your business has no visible online presence, this could drive away potential clients, so it is important to monitor reviews and construct well thought-out responses to both positive and negative reviews.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p class="sqsrte-large">We’ve collected, adapted and summarized some best practices and strategies for how to respond to the different types (see our sources at the end of this article).&nbsp;</p><p class="sqsrte-large"><em>Let’s get started!</em></p>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613519857353-JDCTJAHR9J3HUGF5B4MK/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kG87Sfbgg29A4BYEDq3OXvgUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcf4OxbJOyh_wHUnyc4kQLQ6SBshRGOku7c30Y_IRDNPta8R2IY5BHMaEj1zOWoDTZ/shutterstock_284496374.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1000x667" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="shutterstock_284496374.jpg" data-load="false" data-image-id="602c753769d4f3068ceaa347" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613519857353-JDCTJAHR9J3HUGF5B4MK/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kG87Sfbgg29A4BYEDq3OXvgUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcf4OxbJOyh_wHUnyc4kQLQ6SBshRGOku7c30Y_IRDNPta8R2IY5BHMaEj1zOWoDTZ/shutterstock_284496374.jpg?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<h1><em>﻿</em>Positive Reviews</h1><p class="sqsrte-large">Customers read your reviews before doing business with you and the more highly-rated reviews there are, the more customers your business will attract. </p><p class="sqsrte-large"><em>But positive reviews are not the ones harming your business so why respond to them? </em></p><p class="sqsrte-large">Well, your customers took time out of their busy day to write a review that would benefit your business, so it is crucial that you show your appreciation. They are guiding other potential customers to your business and showing that you value your current customers will increase the chances of those customers returning and/or telling other people about you. </p><p class="sqsrte-large">Here are some guidelines for responding to a positive review:&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>Start by thanking them&nbsp;</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Let them know you are grateful they had a positive experience and personalize the response by addressing them by name at least once. Do not copy and paste the same response you used with another reviewer; every response should be somewhat unique or else it comes off as careless.&nbsp;</p><h4>Here is an example:</h4>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528019948-CEABF8AW5UTN22QBCBWB/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kEFcVTiVtKXrEr_UYTwx8vUUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKchHZzEUojVyUUX0jTugpsDNIXi8PiS-N6eRSWr8NcKQ6cMPVOPWAZNyn0HsxCueKk/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+8.38.19+PM.png" data-image-dimensions="1414x272" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="Screen Shot 2021-02-16 at 8.38.19 PM.png" data-load="false" data-image-id="602c7bd35775d773834e61e3" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528019948-CEABF8AW5UTN22QBCBWB/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kEFcVTiVtKXrEr_UYTwx8vUUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKchHZzEUojVyUUX0jTugpsDNIXi8PiS-N6eRSWr8NcKQ6cMPVOPWAZNyn0HsxCueKk/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+8.38.19+PM.png?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<h3><em>﻿</em><strong>Refer back to specific points in their review &nbsp;</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Referring back to what they wrote shows that you took the time to carefully read what they wrote and are personalizing your response specifically for them.&nbsp;</p><h4>Here is an example:</h4>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613527964016-LBA16II7GMYBNQJ1JMG5/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kNcuw6L41UyNAgU8jaE4z18UqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcDrbmgBX6aPrtQpYs90H4_NVsbbBP7eduHXJGFQx23D13Nf2rk7oVHMX4Xn0H5d1u/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+8.41.32+PM.png" data-image-dimensions="1414x239" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="Screen Shot 2021-02-16 at 8.41.32 PM.png" data-load="false" data-image-id="602c7b9b7079511057aff7b3" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613527964016-LBA16II7GMYBNQJ1JMG5/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kNcuw6L41UyNAgU8jaE4z18UqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcDrbmgBX6aPrtQpYs90H4_NVsbbBP7eduHXJGFQx23D13Nf2rk7oVHMX4Xn0H5d1u/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+8.41.32+PM.png?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<h3><strong>Mention your business&nbsp;</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Make sure to casually name-drop your business name in order to boost the likelihood of appearing in search results.</p><h4>Here is an example:</h4>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613527933596-GDRWB7L7U1NOKFETUR3Z/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kGFdTg4j4cRZSWxI0FczHl8UqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKc0xrKAhg5MoKBc-yGBrXDpEL72h2L363IA2igrrpdXqfRq2qVNxLvBgXSBNuCildn/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.06.57+PM.png" data-image-dimensions="1414x295" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="Screen Shot 2021-02-16 at 9.06.57 PM.png" data-load="false" data-image-id="602c7b7d5775d773834e56f5" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613527933596-GDRWB7L7U1NOKFETUR3Z/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kGFdTg4j4cRZSWxI0FczHl8UqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKc0xrKAhg5MoKBc-yGBrXDpEL72h2L363IA2igrrpdXqfRq2qVNxLvBgXSBNuCildn/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.06.57+PM.png?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<h3><strong>Give customers a reason to come back&nbsp;</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Don't just say “we hope to see you again”; offer them something of value to actually make them want to return such as a money-off coupon for their next purchase or you could highlight something about your company people are not aware of.&nbsp;</p><h4>Here is an example:</h4>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613527765479-WNWICB2P232RJ8HWST8X/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kNmjSplV8kMbse5prS4pBTsUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcqFo20oJLGkK9rd2B-O6XPqpSKFMy4c3OoKw317cscfFK4_0fQ2e-lM0dOvTWaXcU/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.09.14+PM.png" data-image-dimensions="1414x360" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="Screen Shot 2021-02-16 at 9.09.14 PM.png" data-load="false" data-image-id="602c7ad534b03667cbacc511" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613527765479-WNWICB2P232RJ8HWST8X/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kNmjSplV8kMbse5prS4pBTsUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcqFo20oJLGkK9rd2B-O6XPqpSKFMy4c3OoKw317cscfFK4_0fQ2e-lM0dOvTWaXcU/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.09.14+PM.png?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class="sqsrte-large"></p><h1>Negative Reviews&nbsp;</h1><p class="sqsrte-large">When running a business, receiving negative reviews is inevitable, but it’s the way you choose to deal with them that makes the difference. </p><p class="sqsrte-large">If you choose to ignore all the bad reviews, it communicates that you are not capable of taking responsibility. Responding to a negative review is your opportunity to make things right and explain that what happened is an uncommon incident and how you plan to fix it, promising a better experience. </p><p class="sqsrte-large">It's important to invite them back and humanize your response. Plus, if things go well and the concerns are dealt with, then the customer will likely go back and retract their statement.&nbsp; </p>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528213942-UWBXS02D1VRI3WB2VCZV/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kIwgJoN040qxxzeHMZIwZOoUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKckspqLca9B0W1Uj4Uexx_sPiVSVZ69rAnIh0TI8KhWp_XueBWosC8T82A0tLck4LS/shutterstock_1140655919.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1000x516" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="shutterstock_1140655919.jpg" data-load="false" data-image-id="602c7c95330a7a4125669eba" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528213942-UWBXS02D1VRI3WB2VCZV/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kIwgJoN040qxxzeHMZIwZOoUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKckspqLca9B0W1Uj4Uexx_sPiVSVZ69rAnIh0TI8KhWp_XueBWosC8T82A0tLck4LS/shutterstock_1140655919.jpg?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<p class="sqsrte-large">Here are some guidelines for responding to a negative review:&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>Take full responsibility and apologize</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Your customer is upset because of their experience so it is important that you validate their feelings and don’t make excuses, even if it's a very rare situation.&nbsp;</p><h4>Here is an example:</h4>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528357261-9VWQGTYYTIM9ZXJ3R359/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kNhoSXsNEY3qPnU1pR_40IgUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKchRvHrnjWe06IkfYQ4M8f8medHJ98MjlvKrNTga3o-IIKunvPHuIGmHRjKSmWfkUu/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.18.57+PM.png" data-image-dimensions="1292x198" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="Screen Shot 2021-02-16 at 9.18.57 PM.png" data-load="false" data-image-id="602c7d24b8e6443d7b36074c" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528357261-9VWQGTYYTIM9ZXJ3R359/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kNhoSXsNEY3qPnU1pR_40IgUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKchRvHrnjWe06IkfYQ4M8f8medHJ98MjlvKrNTga3o-IIKunvPHuIGmHRjKSmWfkUu/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.18.57+PM.png?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<p class="sqsrte-large"><em>﻿</em>If you believe the customer has clearly misunderstood the situation, carefully clarify and explain how they can resolve the issue without invalidating the customer’s experience and remain apologetic for the confusion. You can even ask if they have any suggestions for how you can make the customer experience easier/prevent future issues of this nature with other customers.</p><h3><strong>Emphasize that this doesn't usually happen</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Make sure to remind the reviewer, or whomever may be reading your reviews, that most of the experiences are positive - still, without invalidating or belittling their experience. </p><h4>Here is an example of what you can write, following the part above:&nbsp;</h4>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528479796-UVCBF18IKTQZ6MK89LCU/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kG5HCcmN8ZkoUQpxZ80EzioUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcjZ_kdFci9aQmsE4A5YzO7ssdwZ2C55iCFTgm8XQ6_xJu9Z27QVjrzzWjZgk_JowS/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.21.06+PM.png" data-image-dimensions="1360x192" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="Screen Shot 2021-02-16 at 9.21.06 PM.png" data-load="false" data-image-id="602c7d9f4271901443a5bcb4" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528479796-UVCBF18IKTQZ6MK89LCU/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kG5HCcmN8ZkoUQpxZ80EzioUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcjZ_kdFci9aQmsE4A5YzO7ssdwZ2C55iCFTgm8XQ6_xJu9Z27QVjrzzWjZgk_JowS/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.21.06+PM.png?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<h3><em>﻿</em><strong>Offer solutions&nbsp;</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Remember this is your opportunity to fix things. This includes providing contact information and referring them to someone who can help them solve their issue.</p><h4>Here is an example:</h4>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528556610-YRMFBBTZ2DB8QKK55XQ7/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kCsIeQ569UQ3Vb-xiLE9cJoUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcEuKbdE5FSs0IHJ0JxYOpX9GRvl2frpPRHZyF_7aVa79yTVgWp63ypjwqaEh4Rg4l/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.22.24+PM.png" data-image-dimensions="1428x370" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="Screen Shot 2021-02-16 at 9.22.24 PM.png" data-load="false" data-image-id="602c7dec7079511057b02d63" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528556610-YRMFBBTZ2DB8QKK55XQ7/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kCsIeQ569UQ3Vb-xiLE9cJoUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcEuKbdE5FSs0IHJ0JxYOpX9GRvl2frpPRHZyF_7aVa79yTVgWp63ypjwqaEh4Rg4l/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.22.24+PM.png?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<h3><em>﻿</em><strong>Short response - keep it to the point</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">If you write too long of a response or go into too many details you might say something wrong which would create more disappointment for the reviewer. Keep the response between 2-3 sentences.</p>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528787286-N1FEFOI2O2BOL8TM7Q0T/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kG87Sfbgg29A4BYEDq3OXvgUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcf4OxbJOyh_wHUnyc4kQLQ6SBshRGOku7c30Y_IRDNPta8R2IY5BHMaEj1zOWoDTZ/shutterstock_1660489855.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1000x667" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="shutterstock_1660489855.jpg" data-load="false" data-image-id="602c7ed2c1532b66c5907b3b" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528787286-N1FEFOI2O2BOL8TM7Q0T/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kG87Sfbgg29A4BYEDq3OXvgUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcf4OxbJOyh_wHUnyc4kQLQ6SBshRGOku7c30Y_IRDNPta8R2IY5BHMaEj1zOWoDTZ/shutterstock_1660489855.jpg?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<h1>Mixed Reviews&nbsp;</h1><p class="sqsrte-large">Most reviews are going to be overwhelmingly positive or negative, but businesses still endure their fair share of mixed reviews. These fall into anything between 2-4 stars, not outstanding but not terrible. Most of these reviews also refer to a mix of pros and cons about the business. </p><p class="sqsrte-large">It's important to acknowledge these because you want to show that you’re all for constructive criticism and always looking for ways to improve. Plus, you are not just speaking to that one reviewer but everyone who reads that review and it will show initiative on your part and your commitment to customer relations. </p><p class="sqsrte-large">Here are some guidelines for responding to a mixed review:&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>Thank the customer for the review&nbsp;</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Even if the review has flaws, it's important to acknowledge the customer intends to help improve your business.&nbsp;</p><h4>Here is an example:</h4>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528877767-S2SQ15SR9EXKIGTSCV7E/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kATPOzpsmaN2TFcsHW4UHPsUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKc0OX9IeHbgjqphZSdJEEvVRO2VZ43OltsNQXMSouRqIzfYp_Ag6dhL-u0JmmWJ8oi/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.27.39+PM.png" data-image-dimensions="1378x246" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="Screen Shot 2021-02-16 at 9.27.39 PM.png" data-load="false" data-image-id="602c7f2d8cdd8b1fd2518713" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528877767-S2SQ15SR9EXKIGTSCV7E/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kATPOzpsmaN2TFcsHW4UHPsUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKc0OX9IeHbgjqphZSdJEEvVRO2VZ43OltsNQXMSouRqIzfYp_Ag6dhL-u0JmmWJ8oi/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.27.39+PM.png?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<h3><em>﻿</em><strong>Acknowledge the positive comments&nbsp;</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">You don't want to overshadow the positive things written so be sure to mention those statements first.&nbsp;</p><h4>Here is an example:</h4>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528964966-B8M1QSQUFL97FIF9PW4Y/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kKlwDFMKH6E-gnGV6GBoZU8UqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcMoESfIBLPTfVrsjVoi2H9d5zsxN8M_NlwhM32EhuR1QP8zyKaAoZ-2V4VJRY2CNk/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.29.12+PM.png" data-image-dimensions="1332x204" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="Screen Shot 2021-02-16 at 9.29.12 PM.png" data-load="false" data-image-id="602c7f84a026094c83cc0674" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613528964966-B8M1QSQUFL97FIF9PW4Y/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kKlwDFMKH6E-gnGV6GBoZU8UqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcMoESfIBLPTfVrsjVoi2H9d5zsxN8M_NlwhM32EhuR1QP8zyKaAoZ-2V4VJRY2CNk/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.29.12+PM.png?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<h3><em>﻿</em><strong>Apologize for the negative comments</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">After acknowledging the positives, make sure you do the same for the negatives and give a brief explanation as to why the issue(s) occurred.&nbsp;</p><h4>Here is an example:</h4>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613529034314-K7G8X5A42DHAXXBVVCZI/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kGrJclnopy1HgT1mfPMmzhwUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcvvOOTIBN-6vO3wJ8avr5U4MGG5sLiAWsdX_V5xy0FSJRtPjjJndIVWCWQT0Uqfkz/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.30.23+PM.png" data-image-dimensions="1386x342" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="Screen Shot 2021-02-16 at 9.30.23 PM.png" data-load="false" data-image-id="602c7fca06ab430190520359" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613529034314-K7G8X5A42DHAXXBVVCZI/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kGrJclnopy1HgT1mfPMmzhwUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcvvOOTIBN-6vO3wJ8avr5U4MGG5sLiAWsdX_V5xy0FSJRtPjjJndIVWCWQT0Uqfkz/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.30.23+PM.png?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<h3><em>﻿</em><strong>Assure a better experience next time</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Most of the time mixed reviewers are not set on never doing business with you again. If you give them hope and helpful and empathetic explanations, then they are likely to try again and hopefully have a much better experience.</p><h4>Here is an example:</h4>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613529091068-TWLCZTPKS3I4WWDBNGKL/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kHCMCCR1hzfRQAQTiFZa8zoUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcelYUbdOdCvl7XHF9Armt-x0T0Dbi98qRIsmkVMR2uH3FzJ-FR695uhEosDNtPhFZ/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.31.19+PM.png" data-image-dimensions="1392x330" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="Screen Shot 2021-02-16 at 9.31.19 PM.png" data-load="false" data-image-id="602c80028cdd8b1fd25199c8" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613529091068-TWLCZTPKS3I4WWDBNGKL/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kHCMCCR1hzfRQAQTiFZa8zoUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcelYUbdOdCvl7XHF9Armt-x0T0Dbi98qRIsmkVMR2uH3FzJ-FR695uhEosDNtPhFZ/Screen+Shot+2021-02-16+at+9.31.19+PM.png?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<p class="sqsrte-large"><em>﻿</em></p><p class="sqsrte-large">Whether a review is positive, negative or mixed, <strong><em>being responsive shows that you are listening and that you appreciate the feedback.</em></strong> The effort you put into responding to reviews can greatly benefit your business and can help attract new clients as well as develop stronger customer relationships. </p><p class="sqsrte-large">And remember - it's impossible for a business to have zero negative reviews and most people are fully aware of this, so the important thing is to make sure you are actively and effectively responding to them. If there is a sea of great reviews and an occasional bad one with a well-constructed explanation and apology, then most people would likely understand and not hold it against your business.</p><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class=""></p><hr /><p class=""><span><strong><em>Sources:</em></strong></span></p><p class=""><a href="https://www.vendasta.com/blog/how-to-respond-reviews-good-bad/"><span><em>Vendasta</em></span></a><em> - sells digital solutions to local businesses</em></p><p class=""><a href="https://www.reviewtrackers.com/guides/examples-responding-reviews/"><span><em>ReviewTrackers</em></span></a><em> - an award-winning customer review software co.</em></p>]]></content:encoded><media:content type="image/jpeg" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613517705049-IEE479RI5Q4OWSWZD5HM/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kG87Sfbgg29A4BYEDq3OXvgUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcf4OxbJOyh_wHUnyc4kQLQ6SBshRGOku7c30Y_IRDNPta8R2IY5BHMaEj1zOWoDTZ/shutterstock_1488336152.jpg?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1000" height="667"><media:title type="plain">Responding to Customer Reviews: A Quick Guide</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>Launch Local at Work: Classic Carolina</title><dc:creator>Leana Sindi</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 04 Feb 2021 13:00:00 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.launchlocal.org/blog/classic-carolina</link><guid isPermaLink="false">5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436:5fedae19fc8ee327ddc3bd64:601afa044b27aa2a6c64fe93</guid><description><![CDATA[By: Leana Sindi

In the midst of the pandemic, small businesses have been amongst the 
economy’s greatest casualties. The Launch Local team is here to help and we 
partnered with Classic Carolina, a brick-and-mortar UNC apparel store. 
Poring over whatever data analytics the store had and our own market 
research, our team devised a game-plan to get Classic Carolina on the 
digital map and improve internal processes.]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="sqsrte-large">Did you know that <strong>small businesses account for 44% of economic activity </strong>in the US? And right now they are struggling. The coronavirus pandemic has hit businesses hard across the board, and according to a Mckinsey report, those amongst the least financially resilient include <strong>1.7 million small businesses</strong>, leaving 20 million workers vulnerable.&nbsp;</p>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613429031449-A228JQMSAZGDVHZ7LI85/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kBxGE22qnnlyLmfy5ebfKgh7gQa3H78H3Y0txjaiv_0fDoOvxcdMmMKkDsyUqMSsMWxHk725yiiHCCLfrh8O1z5QPOohDIaIeljMHgDF5CVlOqpeNLcJ80NK65_fV7S1UXUoWWX-9NUIorTzMboZ1UMXH0Jb7ulEQqQOgWpho5fnJvwGh1qtNWvMhYKnvaKhbA/Screen+Shot+2021-02-15+at+5.43.32+PM.png" data-image-dimensions="1676x1308" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="Screen Shot 2021-02-15 at 5.43.32 PM.png" data-load="false" data-image-id="602af9279cb534098dc42707" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1613429031449-A228JQMSAZGDVHZ7LI85/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kBxGE22qnnlyLmfy5ebfKgh7gQa3H78H3Y0txjaiv_0fDoOvxcdMmMKkDsyUqMSsMWxHk725yiiHCCLfrh8O1z5QPOohDIaIeljMHgDF5CVlOqpeNLcJ80NK65_fV7S1UXUoWWX-9NUIorTzMboZ1UMXH0Jb7ulEQqQOgWpho5fnJvwGh1qtNWvMhYKnvaKhbA/Screen+Shot+2021-02-15+at+5.43.32+PM.png?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<p class="sqsrte-large">	At Launch Local, we have assembled a highly skilled and passionate team to offer free consulting and business services to struggling small businesses across the nation with backgrounds ranging from web/graphic design to professional consulting and financial services.&nbsp;</p><p class="sqsrte-large">Our client, <a href="https://classiccarolinaunc.com/">Classic Carolina</a>, is a family-owned UNC apparel store that sells everything from t-shirts to dog leashes and is best known for their humorous designs and their customer relationships. However, despite the local popularity of this establishment, Classic Carolina did not have the digital tools or online presence that became so important when the pandemic hit. </p><p class="sqsrte-large">When we first approached shop owners Dhruva and Kris Chellani, they explained, <em>“We are a small mom-and-pop shop on Franklin Street. We have a great location and a lot of great products, but we don’t have brand recognition, we have a terrible market presence, and we have an even worse online presence.”</em></p>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1612381339485-QX5QRWYDNKKM9W92Q92L/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kDHPSfPanjkWqhH6pl6g5ph7gQa3H78H3Y0txjaiv_0fDoOvxcdMmMKkDsyUqMSsMWxHk725yiiHCCLfrh8O1z4YTzHvnKhyp6Da-NYroOW3ZGjoBKy3azqku80C789l0mwONMR1ELp49Lyc52iWr5dNb1QJw9casjKdtTg1_-y4jz4ptJBmI9gQmbjSQnNGng/CC2.jpg" data-image-dimensions="2500x1875" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="Pictured: Classic Carolina co-owners, Kris Chellani (left) and Dhruva Chellani (right)." data-load="false" data-image-id="601afc95d5995721c5e27907" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1612381339485-QX5QRWYDNKKM9W92Q92L/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kDHPSfPanjkWqhH6pl6g5ph7gQa3H78H3Y0txjaiv_0fDoOvxcdMmMKkDsyUqMSsMWxHk725yiiHCCLfrh8O1z4YTzHvnKhyp6Da-NYroOW3ZGjoBKy3azqku80C789l0mwONMR1ELp49Lyc52iWr5dNb1QJw9casjKdtTg1_-y4jz4ptJBmI9gQmbjSQnNGng/CC2.jpg?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
          
          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p class=""><em>Pictured: Classic Carolina co-owners, Kris Chellani (left) and Dhruva Chellani (right).</em></p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<p class="sqsrte-large">Our team immediately got to work. Poring over whatever data analytics the store had and our own market research, our head of strategy, Nikita Billman, led a team of LL seeders <em>(our special term for interns, because they plant the seeds for digital growth)</em> in devising a game-plan to get Classic Carolina on the digital map and improve the efficacy of their internal processes.</p><p class="sqsrte-large"><em>“Before we started working with Classic, we learned that Dhruva had been keeping track of inventory in his head for the past 18 years. We had our work cut out for us, but I feel thankful to work with Kris and Dhruva because they were open-minded to learning about digital transformation even though this idea was new to Classic.”</em> - Nikita&nbsp;</p><p class="sqsrte-large">The team identified and carried out 3 key work streams - 1) developing and implementing a digital marketing campaign, 2) re-designing and optimizing the website and 3) putting in place a digital inventory management system.&nbsp;</p><p class=""><br><br><br></p><blockquote><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong><em>“Launch Local has been amazing for us over the past month. They have an outstanding team, made up of the most eager and motivated people I’ve worked with. Their passion for helping small businesses is unmatched and it has made me all the more excited to work on this project. They know exactly what questions to ask and how to get things done quickly.”&nbsp;</em></strong></p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong><em>     -   Kris Chellani, co-owner, Classic Carolina&nbsp;</em></strong></p></blockquote><p class="sqsrte-large"><br><br></p><p class="sqsrte-large">The people behind the Launch Local initiative are driving change forward for small businesses like Classic Carolina and everyone from seeder to upper management is motivated by a passion to help. We spoke to a few of our seeders working the Classic Carolina project and this is what they had to say -&nbsp;</p><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class=""></p>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1612459428024-MZ9MEN5U5N8267KI5E3T/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kLHWC87UFt-pCph4WEjypEtZw-zPPgdn4jUwVcJE1ZvWhcwhEtWJXoshNdA9f1qD7YmDye92LJlx5Z6JHLEUGa26gqpUvI-7KnEGRnZc9flSVe_9EYPkl7gnX2kAgQOByg/LL-intern2-400.png" data-image-dimensions="277x277" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="LL-intern2-400.png" data-load="false" data-image-id="601c2da35f058d1c73be81fb" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1612459428024-MZ9MEN5U5N8267KI5E3T/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kLHWC87UFt-pCph4WEjypEtZw-zPPgdn4jUwVcJE1ZvWhcwhEtWJXoshNdA9f1qD7YmDye92LJlx5Z6JHLEUGa26gqpUvI-7KnEGRnZc9flSVe_9EYPkl7gnX2kAgQOByg/LL-intern2-400.png?format=1000w" />
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Devon Triplett</strong>, freshman, UNC-Chapel Hill University, </p><p class="sqsrte-large"><em>majoring in Business Administration and Social Inequality</em></p><p class="sqsrte-large">“I am passionate about assisting minorities in building wealth through business, investing, and personal finance. My desire to support small businesses through the pandemic coupled with my desire to apply the business fundamentals I learn in the classroom to a real world business are what initially drew me to Launch Local. Since joining, it is the people I am able to work with and the impact we are able to have on small businesses that makes me eager to continue working on projects with Launch Local.”</p><p class="sqsrte-large">“My proudest moment at Launch Local was seeing my client, Kris (co-owner of Classic Carolina), smile and say “wow that is awesome!” following a client presentation. Knowing that the work my team and I did for Kris is going to create value for his small business makes everything worth it!”</p>








  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
