<p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Carson Moore</strong>, freshman, UNC-Chapel Hill University, </p><p class="sqsrte-large"><em>double-majoring in Business Administration and Economics + minoring in Spanish for the Business Professions</em></p><p class="sqsrte-large">“I grew up working alongside my parents on our family farm in Idaho. A strong connection to family and the outdoors has certainly shaped who I am today. Originally, I was drawn to Launch Local because it offered the opportunity to apply the skills I've learned in the classroom to real-world engagement. Since joining, this has grown to include the connections that I am able to make with others who are part of the organization.”</p><p class="sqsrte-large">“I was drawn to the Classic Carolina engagement because it was an opportunity to help a small main-street business that had clearly been hit hard by the pandemic. I think our work on the engagement is going to allow Classic Carolina to reach a larger base of customers and better differentiate itself from the competition.”&nbsp;</p>








  

    
  
    

      

      
