        </figure>
      

    
  


  


<p class="sqsrte-large"><strong><em>“I bought it because I saw it on TikTok!” </em></strong></p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong><em>“Their Instagram feed was just so aesthetically pleasing!” </em></strong></p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong><em>“The video had so many shares on Facebook so I had to check it out!”</em></strong></p><p class="sqsrte-large">If you have heard or said these phrases yourself, that means the business/user has successfully marketed their product! Social media undeniably plays an influential role in our lives. With technology becoming more and more advanced with every passing day, we have become dependent on our devices to keep us in touch with the world. What started out as a mode of keeping in touch with our friends and family, has joined forces with the business world and is used for a whole array of marketing strategies. </p><p class="sqsrte-large">In this post, we’ll be looking at <strong>marketing tips for three specific apps: TikTok, Instagram &amp; Facebook.</strong></p><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class="sqsrte-large"></p><h3><strong>TikTok</strong></h3><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Released in September of 2016, TikTok is a social media platform that lets users create a variety of short videos with a wide variety of genres, ranging from comedy and dance, to education and promotions.</p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">One of the reasons why TikTok has become one of the biggest media platforms is due to the constant entertainment of these short videos. The videos are curated towards the users’ likes retention rate, but this doesn’t mean the user can always know what to expect. Because of the easy-to-use features, micro-entertainment, and its predecessors — Musically &amp; Vine — TikTok is now one of the most popular social platforms among Generation Z.</p></li></ul><h4><strong>Tick-Tock, It’s Time to Get Creative!</strong></h4><ol data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Create your own channel &amp; upload videos advertising your product.</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Making a TikTok is the first step in providing your customers with insight into your business and showing them what you’re all about. People love to watch transformational videos, so some TikTok ideas could be: “How I Package Orders!” or “Watch Me Create [insert product]!”</p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">If you can find a way to encourage your customers to share videos of themselves using or interacting with your products in some way, you’re likely to get a more successful response.</p></li></ul></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Keep in touch with what is trending &amp; try to tie that into your TikToks.</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Although this is not a necessity, using trends that are popular will increase engagement. This can be something as simple as using the same song that is trending in your videos (for instance, Olivia Rodrigo’s <em>Drivers License</em>).</p></li></ul></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Hashtags. Hashtags. Hashtags. Did I mention hashtags?</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Hashtags help categorize the video to cater to different audiences. So if your business was a clothing store centered in San Francisco, you should use “#clothing #SanFrancisco #style #fyp” and so forth. This is also not required for your video to gain attention but it definitely helps more than not putting anything!</p></li></ul></li></ol><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class="sqsrte-large"></p><h3><strong>Instagram</strong></h3><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Happy Belated 10th Birthday to Instagram! Launched in October 2010, Instagram has now accumulated over one billion users. This app is used to stay updated with the lives of our friends, families, and favorite celebrities. With a heavy emphasis on photo and video sharing, Instagram has evolved throughout the years and has become a huge brand marketing platform. New updates have been added such as stories, highlight reels, and a shopping tab which all help users to be exposed to different accounts and businesses.</p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Often referred to as the “simplified version of Facebook”, Instagram is a social network that lets you see how many followers you have, how many you are following, how many likes you have on each photo, and so forth. It is an app that is big on numbers and creating the perfect image for our followers to see.</p></li></ul><h4><strong>Pics or It Didn’t Happen</strong></h4><ol data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Personal to Business Account</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Instagram has a feature that lets you change the type of account you have. The perks of turning your account into a business account, are that you can access the data analytics of your posts, separate your messaging inboxes and display your contact information on your profile.</p></li></ul></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Aesthetic Content</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Since Instagram focuses on photos and videos, it’s important to generate visually compelling content that entails what your brand is and shows your products. To keep your audience engaged, try to include a variety of content, whether that be quotes or instructional posts.</p></li></ul></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Use Story Highlights</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Story Highlights are placed at the bottom of your Instagram bio and are immediately seen when a user visits your profile. Knowing this, it’s important to create different categories that you would want potential consumers to visit to learn more information quicker. For example, if you’re a photography company, different highlight categories could be “Prices,” “Published Work,” “Behind the Scenes,” and so on.</p></li></ul></li></ol><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class=""></p><h3><strong>Facebook</strong></h3><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">What started as a website intended for Harvard students to communicate has become the most popular social media platform worldwide today. Originally launched as “TheFacebook” in 2004, the platform currently sits at more than 2.7 billion monthly active users. This social networking site makes it easy for users to connect and share with friends and family online.</p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Over the years, the platform has integrated businesses by including ads, promotions, and entertainment. It has become easy to sell your product and enhance your own business on Facebook as it is easier to use than other platforms and has been around for longer. Although the younger generations would undoubtedly say that Facebook is used for older generations, it still plays an influential role in the social networking world.</p></li></ul><h4><strong>*Gently Pokes You*</strong></h4><ol data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Create a Facebook Business Page</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Similar to Instagram’s business features, Facebook has an option to create your own business page that will allow you to add a “call-to-action” button, create your own username, see who views your page, and so on.</p></li></ul></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Keep Them Engaged</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Facebook is about building relationships so don’t focus too much on self-promotion when you should be building value for your followers. For example, creating instructional videos, polling your followers, answering questions and taking into account the concerns of your followers, will help you build a more stable relationship with your followers and extend your reach.</p></li></ul></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Link Your Website</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">With so many Internet users that are only increasing, it’s easy to run into website traffic. By creating your own website and including an option to stay connected through Facebook, users can easily become customers and switch back and forth between your Facebook Page and your website for more info.</p><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class=""></p></li></ul></li></ol><p class="sqsrte-large">These are just a few tips for each of these social platforms and there are an abundance of strategies out there that will surely help you promote your business. Finding the strategies that are perfect for you and your business is essential in establishing your brand. Remember, sell the problem you solved and not the product!</p><p class=""><br></p>]]></content:encoded><media:content type="image/png" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1610594858364-NFR0X75GFQE1CLT1YJPZ/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kGaBSG_GrSGuYbxg0Fmwfm17gQa3H78H3Y0txjaiv_0fDoOvxcdMmMKkDsyUqMSsMWxHk725yiiHCCLfrh8O1z5QPOohDIaIeljMHgDF5CVlOqpeNLcJ80NK65_fV7S1UV8hQ1sHl94AUXCoTX2uWSqwqjJZ-JybtKM2u03GsfhAZDqXZYzu2fuaodM4POSZ4w/marketing+tips+2.PNG?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1500" height="840"><media:title type="plain">Tips for Top Social Media Platforms</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>Improve Your Social Media Presence</title><dc:creator>Hiral Patel</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 04 Sep 2020 17:15:00 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.launchlocal.org/blog/social-media-presence</link><guid isPermaLink="false">5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436:5fedae19fc8ee327ddc3bd64:5fedae19fc8ee327ddc3bd65</guid><description><![CDATA[By: Hiral Patel

The power of social media to take businesses to new levels is incredible. 
Social media makes it easier for friends and family to support your 
business while also displaying your products to new customers. As you 
establish your social media presence, we have curated a list of ideas to 
keep in mind.]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="sqsrte-large">The power of social media to take businesses to new levels is incredible. Social media makes it easier for friends and family to support your business while also displaying your products to new customers. People are constantly on social media throughout the day, so it’s important that businesses invest their time in creating a strong social media presence. </p><p class="sqsrte-large">As you establish your social media presence, we have curated a list of ideas to keep in mind.</p><h3><strong>1. Have a Strategy</strong></h3><p class="">Decide on the following before you start to revamp your social media…</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Who your target audience is going to be</p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Which platforms you plan to use</p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">What kind of content you want to post: <a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/briansutter/2017/07/14/21-ideas-for-social-media-content-for-your-small-business/?sh=7f6faeda3011">content ideas source: Forbes</a></p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">How often you will post</p></li></ul><h3><strong>2. Use Multiple Platforms</strong></h3><p class="">Using multiple platforms will broaden your reach and help you get noticed…</p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Instagram - </strong>Target audience includes people who are below 50 years old</p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Facebook - </strong>Great for all audiences</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><a href="https://www.dummies.com/business/marketing/social-media-marketing/how-to-claim-a-facebook-places-page-for-your-business/">How to gain access</a></p></li></ul><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>TikTok - </strong>Target audience includes people who are below 30 years old</p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>LinkedIn - </strong>Great for those whose target audience is other businesses or professionals</p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Twitter - </strong>Great way to interact with local community members and potential customers</p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Pinterest - </strong>Great for restaurants, fashion, art, travel, and event-planning oriented businesses</p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>YouTube - </strong>Great for products that require a guide: tutorials on how to use your product or videos on how the product is produced</p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Yelp -</strong> Applicable for any business that has a physical storefront</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><a href="https://www.yelp-support.com/article/How-do-I-claim-a-business-page?l=en_US">How to gain access</a></p></li></ul><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong>Google My Business</strong> <strong>- </strong>Applicable for any business that has a physical storefront</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><a href="https://support.google.com/business/answer/4566671?hl=en">How to gain access</a></p></li></ul><h3><strong>3. Add Social Icons to Emails &amp; Your Website</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong><em>Social media icons on your website and email help increase traffic to your pages</em></strong>, which will help things like search engine optimization (SEO). Icons are small so they don’t distract the customer and also make it easier for customers to learn more about your products. </p><h3><strong>4. Create Content with Your Audience in Mind</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">When you are creating your content, you can use the “<a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/briansutter/2017/07/14/21-ideas-for-social-media-content-for-your-small-business/?sh=7f6faeda3011">what kind of content to post</a>” resource. </p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong><em>You should create posts with your audience in mind in order to keep them interested.</em></strong> Customers follow your page because they want to stay informed about new products or sales. If your posts tend to be unengaging or off-topic, customers will begin to unfollow you.</p><h3><strong>5. Maintain Presence&nbsp;</strong></h3><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Do some research on what the most popular time and day to scroll among your target audience is</p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Post to your social media regularly, preferably weekly, whether it be stories or posts</p></li></ul><h3><strong>6. Use Apps to Schedule Posts</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong><em>Use an app that allows you to schedule posts</em></strong> to Instagram, Twitter, and Pinterest. One such app is <a href="https://later.com/"><strong><em>Later</em></strong></a>. </p><p class="">The benefits of using these apps include…</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Not having to create social media content in real time - create content in one day for the rest of the week/month/etc.</p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Not having to remember or make time for posting to social media every day - the app can do it for you by scheduling posts in advance </p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">Use their analytics tools to see how your posts performed - level of engagement on different posts, best posting times etc. </p></li></ul><h3><strong>7. Engage with Your Audience</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Engaging with your followers and potential followers is important in <strong><em>showing your customers you care about them and their feedback</em></strong>. It allows you to gain trust and interest in your business. </p><p class="">When you aren’t posting, you should be…</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">sharing posts</p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">asking questions</p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">addressing complaints</p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">liking posts and comments, etc.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>8. Hashtags</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Using hashtags is one of the easiest ways to bring traffic to your page. </p><p class="sqsrte-large"><em>Example: If you own a jewelry store in SoHo, Manhattan, you’ll want new customers in that area to stumble upon your page when they search #sohojewelry and #sohoshopping</em> </p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong><em>Make sure you are not using hashtags excessively; the average number of hashtags businesses use is ~11.&nbsp;&nbsp;</em></strong></p><p class="sqsrte-large">Hashtags also help engage people with your brand. <strong><em>Create a specific hashtag for your business</em></strong>, so when customers share your product to their own social media they can use the hashtag. This will…</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large">allow people to click on the hashtag and find your posts, as well as other people’s posts. </p></li><li><p class="sqsrte-large">make it easier to interact with customers and re-share. </p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="sqsrte-large"><em>Example: If your jewelry store was named Ruby Designs and located in Westlake, Seattle, your business specific hashtag could be #RubyDesignsSeattle or #RubyWestlake</em></p></li></ul></li></ul><h3><strong>9. Share Reviews</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Ask your customers to share their purchases with their friends on social media. Your email confirmation page or physical receipt is a great place to add this. </p><p class="sqsrte-large"><strong><em>Share their posts to your pages as well as reviews</em></strong> they may have written on Google Reviews, Yelp, etc. Customers love this because it makes them feel acknowledged. This will also help affirm to potential customers that existing customers are happy with your product/service.</p><h3><strong>10. Customer Service</strong></h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Many customers will comment their issues on your posts or tell you them through direct message. In order to keep customers happy, <strong><em>respond as quickly as possible</em></strong>. This is essential in limiting the spread of negative reviews and providing quality customer support.</p><p class="sqsrte-large">In order to measure what’s working and what’s not, you will have to watch for new followers and engagement. Every business is unique, so there is no perfect formula for every business. </p><p class="sqsrte-large">Don’t be afraid to try new ideas to see what works and what doesn’t!</p><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class="sqsrte-large"></p>]]></content:encoded><media:content type="image/jpeg" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1609412417106-0E02HYJQENY8V3J3JJJB/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kLkXF2pIyv_F2eUT9F60jBl7gQa3H78H3Y0txjaiv_0fDoOvxcdMmMKkDsyUqMSsMWxHk725yiiHCCLfrh8O1z4YTzHvnKhyp6Da-NYroOW3ZGjoBKy3azqku80C789l0iyqMbMesKd95J-X4EagrgU9L3Sa3U8cogeb0tjXbfawd0urKshkc5MgdBeJmALQKw/image-asset.jpeg?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1500" height="1000"><media:title type="plain">Improve Your Social Media Presence</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>Introducing Launch Local</title><dc:creator>Guest User</dc:creator><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2020 17:05:00 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.launchlocal.org/blog/introducing-launch-local</link><guid isPermaLink="false">5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436:5fedae19fc8ee327ddc3bd64:5fedae19fc8ee327ddc3bd69</guid><description><![CDATA[Our mission and story]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class=""><strong>Launch Local </strong>was started to empower small businesses by helping them adopt the necessary digital infrastructure to sustain their operations and improve sales. Small businesses, the foundation of America’s economy, have been hit hard during COVID-19, and our goal is to work with them to build digital resilience for the inevitable change in customer expectations in the new normal.</p><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class=""></p><p class="">We are a group of volunteers looking to empower small businesses and non-profits across the country to build sustainable digital platforms. </p><p class="">During the COVID-19 Pandemic, many small businesses across the nation struggled as traffic to their stores dramatically fell. These small businesses, the foundation of America’s economy, unfortunately at times lack the digital expertise and horsepower to stay afloat. We built <strong>Launch Local, </strong>a two-sided platform, to help small businesses and nonprofits rethink and implement new digital programs.  At the same time, Launch Local creates new opportunities for college students, “seeders” as we say, to learn about digital growth and implementation in a way that also gives back to local communities.   </p><p class="">Our team comes from consulting to high tech, and we bring our skills together to provide the best impact for local businesses, completely free. </p>]]></content:encoded><media:content type="image/png" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fd6d3753c1f627580a14436/1610705134138-O28NTGSASTO0J1FWQA9V/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kLvO88XaRQOvvjlb-FXAvCMUqsxRUqqbr1mOJYKfIPR7LoDQ9mXPOjoJoqy81S2I8N_N4V1vUb5AoIIIbLZhVYxCRW4BPu10St3TBAUQYVKcHOqXV0Y70bOzhFl6IHyVBfnARZs3uzkzfcs_TbJn53E5c7mERvlbNEYC4RApYsyK/Untitled_Artwork%2B3.png?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1000" height="559"><media:title type="plain">Introducing Launch Local</media:title></media:content></item></channel></rss>